    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36654 mentions that https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33771 is needed in order to really close this, so that users can opt-in if they *really* want home dir as a root dir.\r\n\r\nWe could merge this as a first step after 0.12 release, but otherwise this is blocked by #33771 .\r\n\r\n> I see no reason why we need to treat `HOME` in a special way here. `root_dir` can be a function to address special cases like this one.\r\n\r\nExplained in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36654 . It's a painful footgun and rarely useful, and is the source of >50% of \"performance issues\". There is no way to have `.git` (or other common files) as a root-marker, while also avoiding \"accidental home dir\".\r\n\r\n",
